{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775818498103,"sessionID":"ses_288fc3978ffestAwKqA90pStH5","part":{"id":"prt_d7703def1001WQcUmnnsnvnK9k","messageID":"msg_d7703d2c9001PTA4NteT93D6mO","sessionID":"ses_288fc3978ffestAwKqA90pStH5","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_632dfc0aaaf64862b4bac467","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key subdirectories)\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - read ALL files in this directory and subdirectories\n3. Any existing design.md or design documents\n4. The API types for CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime (look in pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ or similar paths)\n5. Any existing controller implementations for CodeInterpreter or AgentRuntime\n6. The reference code at /tmp/agentcube-ref/ if it exists - especially any workloadmanager or sandbox-related code\n7. Any existing lifecycle management, cleanup, or deletion code patterns\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- All files in pkg/workloadmanager/ with their contents summarized\n- API type definitions for CodeInterpreter/AgentRuntime (especially lifecycle-related fields like deletion, finalizers, TTL, etc.)\n- Existing controller patterns\n- Any relevant reference code\n- Testing patterns used in the project","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288fc057cffen71315G5XdcYG2 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the entire project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive AgentCube Project Summary\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                          # SDD prompt configuration\n├── go.mod                                  # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube (Go 1.25.0)\n├── go.sum\n├── design.md                               # AR-003: CRD shared types design\n├── project.md                              # Project context document\n├── delta-spec.md                           # AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP service spec\n├── test_spec.md                            # TDD test specification\n├── coverage.out                            # Coverage output\n│\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/              # CRD type definitions\n│   │   ├── doc.go                          # Package markers (+k8s:deepcopy-gen, +groupName)\n│   │   ├── groupversion_info.go            # GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, Kind constants\n│   │   ├── groupversion_info_test.go       # Scheme registration tests\n│   │   ├── agent_type.go                   # AgentRuntime CRD types\n│   │   ├── agent_type_test.go              # AgentRuntime tests\n│   │   ├── codeinterpreter_types.go        # CodeInterpreter CRD types\n│   │   ├── codeinterpreter_types_test.go   # CodeInterpreter tests (654 lines)\n│   │   ├── shared_types.go                 # Shared types (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType)\n│   │   ├── shared_types_test.go            # Shared type tests\n│   │   ├── constants.go                    # Shared constants (annotation keys)\n│   │   ├── constants_test.go               # Constant tests\n│   │   └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go        # Auto-generated DeepCopy methods\n│   │\n│   └── workloadmanager/\n│       ├── handler/\n│       │   ├── sandbox_create.go           # Sandbox creation handlers (687 lines)\n│       │   ├── models.go                   # Request/Response DTOs\n│       │   └── constants.go                # GVRs, labels, annotations, defaults\n│       └── response/\n│           ├── response.go                 # JSON/Error response helpers\n│           └── response_test.go            # Response helper tests\n│\n├── client-go/                              # Generated Kubernetes client code (fake/stub implementations)\n│   ├── clientset/\n│   │   ├── clientset.go                    # Interface definition\n│   │   ├── fake.go                         # Fake clientset\n│   │   └── typed/runtime/v1alpha1/         # Typed client interfaces\n│   └── informers/externalversions/         # Informer factory (fake/stub)\n│\n├── changes/                                # Change proposals (AR-001 through AR-006)\n│   ├── AR-001/                             # AgentRuntime CRD type definition\n│   ├── AR-002/                             # CodeInterpreter CRD type definition\n│   ├── AR-003/                             # CRD shared types and constants\n│   ├── AR-004/                             # WorkloadManager HTTP service framework\n│   ├── AR-005/                             # Sandbox creation handler (stub design)\n│   └── AR-006/                             # Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management (stub design, detailed delta-spec)\n│\n├── sandbox-orchestration/                  # Sandbox orchestration design + spec\n├── session-routing/                        # Router/session routing design\n├── session-store/                          # Redis/Valkey session store design\n├── idle-cleanup/                           # Agentd idle cleanup controller design\n├── code-execution/                         # PicoD code execution design\n├── cli-toolkit/                            # CLI toolkit design\n├── python-sdk/                             # Python SDK design\n├── deployment/                             # Deployment design\n├── ci-cd/                                  # CI/CD design\n├── integrations/                           # Integrations design\n├── testing/                                # TDD manifest\n└── delta-spec.md                           # AR-004 delta spec\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. pkg/workloadmanager/ - All Files Summarized\n\n#### 2.1 `handler/constants.go` (53 lines)\nDefines all GVRs, Kind constants, labels, annotations, and default values:\n- **GVRs**: `AgentRuntimeGVR`, `CodeInterpreterGVR`, `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes), `SandboxClaimGVR` (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxclaims)\n- **Kind constants**: `AgentRuntimeKind`, `CodeInterpreterKind`, `SandboxesKind`, `SandboxClaimsKind`\n- **Labels**: `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by=agentcube-workload-manager`, `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`, `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name`\n- **Annotations**: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`, `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n- **Defaults**: `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8` (hours), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15` (minutes)\n- **Identity**: `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`, `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n\n#### 2.2 `handler/models.go` (57 lines)\nDefines request/response DTOs:\n- `CreateSandboxRequest`: Kind, Name, Namespace (with Validate method)\n- `CreateSandboxResponse`: SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints\n- `EntryPoint`: Path, Protocol, Endpoint\n- `SandboxInfo`: Full sandbox metadata including SessionID, SandboxName, SandboxID, WorkloadName, Namespace, Kind, PodIP, EntryPoints, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status\n- `SandboxStatus`: Status string + Error (for watcher channels)\n\n#### 2.3 `handler/sandbox_create.go` (687 lines)\nThe core sandbox creation handler with two main methods:\n- **`CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`**: Creates a Sandbox CR from an AgentRuntime template\n  - Looks up AgentRuntime via informer lister\n  - Generates session ID (UUID) and sandbox name (`{workloadName}-{8 random chars}`)\n  - Builds unstructured Sandbox CR with labels, annotations (idle-timeout), lifecycle (shutdownTime = now + TTL)\n  - Stores sandbox info, watches for running status (2-minute timeout)\n  - Resolves Pod IP, builds entry points, updates store\n  - Rollback on failure (deletes CR)\n\n- **`CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox`**: Creates Sandbox or SandboxClaim from CodeInterpreter template\n  - If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: creates `SandboxClaim` CR (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io) with minimal metadata\n  - If `WarmPoolSize == 0`: creates full `Sandbox` CR with container spec (name: \"code-interpreter\")\n  - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var when `AuthMode == picod`\n  - Same watch/rollback pattern as AgentRuntime\n\n- **Helper methods**:\n  - `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()`: Converts AgentRuntime template to unstructured Sandbox CR\n  - `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()`: Converts CodeInterpreter template to Sandbox or SandboxClaim CR\n  - `rollbackCR()`: Deletes CR on failure (30-second timeout, ignores NotFound)\n  - `resolvePodIP()`: Multi-strategy Pod IP resolution (direct lookup, annotation, owner reference)\n  - `injectPicodAuthEnv()`: Injects public key from K8s Secret into container env\n  - `buildEntryPoints()`: Constructs endpoint URLs from Pod IP and ports\n  - `getDynamicClient()`: Auth-aware client selection (per-user or in-cluster)\n\n- **Interfaces** (dependency injection):\n  - `Store`: StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox\n  - `SandboxReconcilerWatcher`: WatchSandboxOnce\n  - `TokenCache`: GetOrCreateUserK8sClient\n  - `UserClientFactory`: CreateUserClient\n\n#### 2.4 `response/response.go` (45 lines)\nHTTP response helpers using Gin:\n- `JSON()`: 200 with SuccessResponse{Data, Message}\n- `Created()`: 201 with SuccessResponse\n- `Error()`: Custom HTTP code with ErrorResponse{Error, Code}\n- `ErrorWithID()`: Same + RequestID\n\n#### 2.5 `response/response_test.go` (108 lines)\nTests using `gin.CreateTestContext()` + `httptest.NewRecorder()`:\n- TestJSON_Success, TestCreated_Success\n- TestError_BadRequest, TestError_NotFound, TestError_Internal\n- TestError_WithRequestID\n- All use `testify/assert` for assertions\n\n---\n\n### 3. Design Documents\n\n| Document | Location | Summary |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **Main Design** | `design.md` | AR-003: Extracting shared types (TargetPort, ProtocolType) into dedicated files |\n| **AR-001** | `changes/AR-001/design.md` | AgentRuntime CRD type definition - full spec with kubebuilder markers, API contract, testing strategy |\n| **AR-002** | `changes/AR-002/design.md` | CodeInterpreter CRD type definition - flat template fields, WarmPoolSize, AuthMode |\n| **AR-003** | `changes/AR-003/design.md` | Shared types (ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort) extraction |\n| **AR-004** | `changes/AR-004/design.md` | WorkloadManager HTTP service framework - full CRUD API design, routing, error handling, testing |\n| **AR-005** | `changes/AR-005/design.md` | Sandbox creation handler - **stub** (TODO placeholders) |\n| **AR-006** | `changes/AR-006/design.md` | Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management - **stub** (empty sections) |\n| **Sandbox Orchestration** | `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` | Comprehensive reference of all packages, types, reconciler, garbage collector |\n| **Idle Cleanup** | `idle-cleanup/design.md` | Agentd reconciler for idle sandbox cleanup (15-min timeout) |\n| **Session Routing** | `session-routing/design.md` | Router with JWT auth, reverse proxy, session manager |\n| **Session Store** | `session-store/design.md` | Redis/Valkey store interface and implementations |\n| **Delta Spec (AR-004)** | `delta-spec.md` | Gherkin-style requirements for WorkloadManager HTTP service |\n| **Delta Spec (AR-006)** | `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md` | **Detailed** Gherkin requirements for sandbox deletion + GC (326 lines) |\n\n---\n\n### 4. API Type Definitions for CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime\n\n#### AgentRuntime (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`)\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort     `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\"`            // Required - embeds corev1.PodSpec\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`     // Default: 15m\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"` // Default: 8h\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels      map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    Spec        corev1.PodSpec    `json:\"spec\"`  // Full Kubernetes PodSpec\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`)\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort                    `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration                `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`     // Default: 15m\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration                `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"` // Default: 8h\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32                          `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`       // Default: 0\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType                    `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`           // \"picod\" or \"none\"\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {  // FLAT fields (not full PodSpec)\n    Labels           map[string]string             `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations      map[string]string             `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string                       `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n    Image            string                        `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullPolicy  corev1.PullPolicy             `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n    Environment      []corev1.EnvVar               `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n    Command          []string                      `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args             []string                      `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements   `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    Ready      bool               `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Shared Types (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`)\n```go\ntype ProtocolType string\nconst ( ProtocolTypeHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"; ProtocolTypeHTTPS = \"HTTPS\" )\n\ntype AuthModeType string\nconst ( AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"; AuthModeNone = \"none\" )\n\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    Name       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Lifecycle-Related Fields Summary\n| Field | Type | Default | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|---------|\n| `SessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | 15m | Idle timeout before sandbox cleanup |\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | 8h | Maximum sandbox lifetime (TTL) |\n| `WarmPoolSize` | `*int32` | 0 | Pre-warmed sandbox pool (CodeInterpreter only) |\n| `AuthMode` | `AuthModeType` | \"\" | Authentication mode (CodeInterpreter only) |\n\n**Note**: There are NO explicit finalizer, deletionTimestamp, or TTL fields on the CRD types themselves. Lifecycle is managed through:\n1. `MaxSessionDuration` -> translated to `shutdownTime` in the Sandbox CR's `spec.lifecycle`\n2. `SessionTimeout` -> translated to `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` annotation on Sandbox\n3. The `last-activity-time` annotation (read by agentd controller for idle cleanup)\n4. A background garbage collector (15-second tick) that queries Store for expired/inactive sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing Controller Implementations\n\n**No actual controller .go files exist in the source tree.** However, the design documents describe several controllers:\n\n#### 5.1 SandboxReconciler (described in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`)\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme   *runtime.Scheme\n    watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n    mu       sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n- Watches Sandbox CRs for `Ready` condition becoming `True`\n- Notifies waiter channels (buffer 1, non-blocking send)\n- Used by `SandboxCreateHandler` via `WatchSandboxOnce()` interface\n\n#### 5.2 CodeInterpreter Controller (described in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`)\n- Reconciles `CodeInterpreter` CRs\n- When `WarmPoolSize > 0`: ensures `SandboxTemplate` and `SandboxWarmPool` resources\n- Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` unless `AuthModeNone`\n- Requeues 5s if public key not cached\n\n#### 5.3 Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (described in `idle-cleanup/design.md`)\n```go\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n```\n- Watches `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox` resources\n- Reads `last-activity-time` annotation\n- Deletes sandbox if `time.Now().After(lastActivity + 15m)`\n- Requeues with `time.Until(expirationTime)` if not yet expired\n- Uses `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n\n#### 5.4 Garbage Collector (described in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` and `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`)\n```go\ntype garbageCollector struct {\n    k8sClient   *K8sClient\n    interval    time.Duration  // 15 seconds\n    storeClient store.Store\n}\n```\n- Background goroutine, 15-second tick interval\n- Per-tick: `ListInactiveSandboxes(cutoff=now-15m, limit=16)` + `ListExpiredSandboxes(cutoff=now, limit=16)`\n- Merges lists, deduplicates by session ID\n- For each: delete CR (NotFound = success), then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` on Store\n- 2-minute timeout per tick\n- Logs success/failure counts\n\n---\n\n### 6. Reference Code at /tmp/agentcube-ref/\n\n**The directory `/tmp/agentcube-ref/` does not exist.** No reference code is available at this path.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Lifecycle Management, Cleanup, and Deletion Code Patterns\n\n#### 7.1 Rollback on Creation Failure (`sandbox_create.go`)\n```go\nfunc (h *SandboxCreateHandler) rollbackCR(ctx context.Context, gvr schema.GroupVersionResource, namespace, name string, dynClient dynamic.Interface) error {\n    rollbackCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 30*time.Second)\n    defer cancel()\n    err := dynClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(namespace).Delete(rollbackCtx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    if err != nil && apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        return nil\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n#### 7.2 Sandbox Lifecycle in Created CRs\n```go\n// TTL -> shutdownTime\nttl := DefaultSandboxTTL  // 8 hours\nif template.Spec.MaxSessionDuration != nil {\n    ttl = template.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration.Hours()\n}\nshutdownTime := time.Now().Add(time.Duration(ttl) * time.Hour)\n\nspec := map[string]interface{}{\n    \"replicas\": int64(1),\n    \"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n        \"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n    },\n}\n\n// Idle timeout annotation\ncr.SetAnnotations(map[string]string{\n    \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\": fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm\", idleTimeout),\n})\n```\n\n#### 7.3 Planned Deletion Handler (from AR-006 delta-spec, NOT yet implemented)\nThe `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md` specifies a `SandboxDeleteHandler` with:\n1. Extract `sessionId` from path parameter\n2. `Store.GetSandboxBySessionID()` to load session info\n3. Select GVR based on `sandboxInfo.Kind`\n4. `dynClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(ns).Delete()` (NotFound = idempotent success)\n5. `Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` to clean Store\n6. Return 200 success\n\n#### 7.4 Planned GC Loop (from AR-006 delta-spec, NOT yet implemented)\n- 15-second tick interval\n- 2-minute per-tick context timeout\n- Query `ListInactiveSandboxes(now - 15m, 16)` and `ListExpiredSandboxes(now, 16)`\n- Deduplicate by session ID\n- Delete CR + clean Store for each\n- Log success/failure counts\n\n---\n\n### 8. Testing Patterns\n\n#### 8.1 Framework and Libraries\n- **Test framework**: `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n- **HTTP testing**: `net/http/httptest` + `gin.CreateTestContext()`\n- **Coverage**: `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out` + `go tool cover -html`\n\n#### 8.2 Test File Organization\nEvery source file has a corresponding `*_test.go` in the same package:\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── agent_type.go          -> agent_type_test.go (235 lines, 8 tests)\n├── codeinterpreter_types.go -> codeinterpreter_types_test.go (654 lines, 28 tests)\n├── shared_types.go        -> shared_types_test.go (77 lines, 6 tests)\n├── constants.go           -> constants_test.go (21 lines, 3 tests)\n├── groupversion_info.go   -> groupversion_info_test.go (80 lines, 7 tests)\n└── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  (auto-generated, no tests)\n\npkg/workloadmanager/response/\n├── response.go            -> response_test.go (108 lines, 6 tests)\n```\n\n#### 8.3 Test Patterns Used\n\n**Scheme Registration Tests:**\n```go\nfunc TestSchemeRegistration(t *testing.T) {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    err := AddToScheme(scheme)\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    gvk := SchemeGroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n    obj, err := scheme.New(gvk)\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.IsType(t, &AgentRuntime{}, obj)\n}\n```\n\n**DeepCopy Isolation Tests:**\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n    original := &AgentRuntime{...}\n    cp := original.DeepCopy()\n    assert.Equal(t, original.Name, cp.Name)\n    cp.Spec.Ports[0].Port = 9090\n    assert.Equal(t, uint32(8080), original.Spec.Ports[0].Port)  // Original unchanged\n}\n```\n\n**HTTP Handler Tests:**\n```go\nfunc TestJSON_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n    w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    c, _ := gin.CreateTestContext(w)\n    JSON(c, http.StatusOK, data)\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n    var resp SuccessResponse\n    json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &resp)\n    assert.Equal(t, data, resp.Data)\n}\n```\n\n**Default/Zero-Value Tests:**\n```go\nfunc TestCodeInterpreterSpecDefaults(t *testing.T) {\n    ci := &CodeInterpreterSpec{Template: &CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate{}}\n    assert.Empty(t, ci.Ports)\n    assert.Nil(t, ci.SessionTimeout)\n    assert.Nil(t, ci.WarmPoolSize)\n}\n```\n\n#### 8.4 TDD Requirements (from `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`)\n- **T/C Ratio**: Must be > 0.4 (40 lines of test per 100 lines of code)\n- **Completeness**: Every source file must have a corresponding test file\n- **Core tests required**:\n  - Test-WM-1: Mock K8s Client, verify sandbox creation\n  - Test-WM-2: Session conflict handling (409 or recover existing)\n  - Test-WM-3: Pod status sync, verify Endpoint returned\n  - Test-WM-4: Physical resource cleanup (K8s Delete + Redis cleanup)\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No actual controller implementations exist** - Only the `sandbox_create.go` HTTP handler exists; the `SandboxReconciler`, `garbageCollector`, and `agentd.Reconciler` are described in design docs but not implemented as Go source files.\n\n2. **AR-005 and AR-006 design docs are stubs** - The actual implementation details live in `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md` (326 lines of Gherkin requirements) rather than the design.md.\n\n3. **No finalizers on CRDs** - Lifecycle management is done through annotations (`idle-timeout`, `last-activity-time`) and the `spec.lifecycle.shutdownTime` field on Sandbox CRs, not through Kubernetes finalizers.\n\n4. **No reference code** at `/tmp/agentcube-ref/`.\n\n5. **The client-go code is stub/fake** - The generated client code contains no-op implementations (e.g., `Start()` is a no-op, `WaitForCacheSync()` returns empty map).\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288fc057cffen71315G5XdcYG2","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775818242688,"end":1775818498100}}}}
